div.p:
There have been isolated cases of anti-foreign agitation, the outstanding
                            case of this kind being in Hwaiking, Honan. Among the following [sic] slogans on the walls of a missionary
                            compound at that place was found the following: 

It is the aim of the revolution to drive out the foreign
                                    devil;

Drive out the foreign devil and recover liberty and
                                    power;

Strike down British Imperialists;

Exterminate the foreigner.
